# 🎨 PixelTales Collaboration Sync — Bug Report & Fix Plan

> **Status:** Documented, Not Yet Implemented  
> **Date:** 2026-07-13  
> **Analyzed by:** Antigravity (Frontend + Mobile Agent)

---

## 🐛 Reported Bugs

### Bug 1 — Canvas Not Synced on Entry
> *"When I go inside the canvas there is no drawing of the other user, but only see cursors and drawings when they stroke"*

**What happens:**  
User B enters the canvas mid-session. The canvas appears blank or shows only their own local data. The other person's existing drawings are invisible. Only new strokes drawn **after** B enters become visible.

### Bug 2 — Clear Canvas Shows Ghost Data on Re-entry
> *"I tried to clear the canvas both of us, and when I go in again I saw some drawings instead of a cleared canvas"*

**What happens:**  
Both users clear the canvas (collaboration `clear` event fires). The in-memory Paper.js canvas is cleared correctly. But when either user navigates away and comes back to the canvas, the **old drawings reappear** because they are still saved in local storage.

### Bug 3 — Shapes / Eraser Not Visible Until Released
> *"It's not consistent — you only see the drawing when they stroke"*

**What happens:**  
Brush strokes are sent in real-time batches (every 10 points or 50ms). However, shapes (rectangle, circle, line, triangle, etc.) and the eraser tool are only sent **once on mouse-up** — meaning the remote user sees nothing until the other person finishes the stroke.

---

## 🔍 Root Cause Analysis

### Bug 1 Root Cause — No Initial State Request on Canvas Entry

**File:** `frontend/src/pages/CanvasDrawingPage.tsx` (~line 783–910)

When the canvas page mounts, it loads canvas data exclusively from **local `storyStore`** (IndexedDB/localStorage). It never requests the live, current canvas state from the other connected user via WebSocket.

The full sync flow (`handle_request_sync` → `request_canvas_state` → `receive_canvas_state`) **exists in the backend** (`consumers.py` lines 842–935) but is **never triggered by the frontend on canvas entry during a live collaboration session**.

```
Current flow on canvas entry:
  Mount → load from storyStore (local) → show stale or empty canvas ❌

Required flow on canvas entry:
  Mount + isCollaborating → request canvas state via WS → receive snapshot → render ✅
```

**Key backend handlers that already exist (unused):**
- `handle_request_sync` (consumers.py:842) — accepts a `request_sync` message, fetches from DB or asks peers
- `handle_canvas_state` (consumers.py:878) — receives a canvas snapshot, saves to DB
- `receive_canvas_state` (consumers.py:924) — delivers snapshot to the requesting user

---

### Bug 2 Root Cause — Clear Event Doesn't Invalidate Local Cache

**File:** `frontend/src/pages/CanvasDrawingPage.tsx` (~line 1750+)  
**File:** `frontend/src/stores/storyStore.ts`

The `canvas_cleared` WebSocket event handler calls `removeChildren()` on the active Paper.js layer — clearing the **in-memory** canvas. However, it does **not** call `saveCanvasData(storyId, pageId, null)` to wipe the locally persisted snapshot.

When the user navigates away and re-enters the canvas, `CanvasDrawingPage` re-initializes and calls `getCanvasData(storyId, pageId)` from `storyStore` — which still returns the **old data** because it was never cleared.

```
Clear event handler (current):
  canvas_cleared → paper.js removeChildren() ✅ | storyStore still has old data ❌

Clear event handler (required):
  canvas_cleared → paper.js removeChildren() ✅ + saveCanvasData(id, pageId, null) ✅
```

---

### Bug 3 Root Cause — Shape/Eraser Tools Are Not Streamed

**File:** `frontend/src/components/canvas/PaperDrawingEngine.ts`

The brush tool uses `continueBrushStroke()` which calls `flushBatchedPoints()` — sending a `draw_batch_progress` message every 10 points or 50ms. This gives real-time feedback.

All other tools send data **only in `handleMouseUp`** via `notifyDrawingComplete()`. The remote user sees nothing until the drawing is finished.

| Tool | When data is sent | Remote experience |
|---|---|---|
| `brush` | Every 10 pts / 50ms | ✅ Real-time smooth |
| `eraser` | On mouse-up only | ❌ Invisible during drag |
| `rectangle` | On mouse-up only | ❌ Invisible during drag |
| `circle` | On mouse-up only | ❌ Invisible during drag |
| `line` | On mouse-up only | ❌ Invisible during drag |
| `triangle/star/heart/arrow` | On mouse-up only | ❌ Invisible during drag |
| `text` | On confirm | ✅ Acceptable |
| `fill` | Immediately | ✅ Real-time |

