### Option B — Recommended Follow-up: Server-Authoritative Snapshot (1-2 days)

This makes the collaboration system truly professional by making the **server** the single source of truth for canvas state.

**Architecture:**

```
Host draws → every 5s → send canvas_state to server (Paper.js JSON export)
Server stores it in canvas_state JSONField (already exists in CollaborationSession model)
Any user enters canvas → server sends latest snapshot
User applies snapshot → then receives/replays any deltas since snapshot
```

**Frontend changes needed:**
1. Auto-save `paper.js exportJSON()` to server every 5 seconds in a `setInterval` during collaboration
2. On canvas entry (`useEffect`), first request server snapshot, then wire up live drawing events

**Backend changes needed:**
1. `handle_canvas_state` (already exists) — stores JSON in `canvas_state` field ✅
2. `handle_request_sync` (already exists) — reads from `canvas_state` and sends back ✅
3. Nothing to add on the backend — it's already built!

The backend plumbing is **100% done**. Only the frontend needs to be wired up.

