### Option C — Shape Preview Streaming (Bug 3 fix, ~3 hours)

Stream shape previews during drag by adding intermediate messages:

**In `PaperDrawingEngine.ts` → `updateShape()` method:**
```typescript
private updateShape(point: paper.Point) {
  // ... existing shape update logic ...
  
  // ✅ NEW: Send shape preview to collaborators during drag
  if (this.onDrawingComplete && this.currentPath && this.shapeStartPoint) {
    this.onDrawingComplete({
      type: 'shape_preview',
      tool: this.currentTool,
      startPoint: { x: this.shapeStartPoint.x, y: this.shapeStartPoint.y },
      endPoint: { x: point.x, y: point.y },
      strokeColor: this.currentColor,
      strokeWidth: this.currentSize,
      filled: this.shapeFilled,
      opacity: this.currentOpacity
    });
  }
}
```

**Remote rendering:** Use a separate `previewLayer` in Paper.js that gets cleared on each `shape_preview` message and redrawn with the new shape. On `mouseup`, replace preview with the final committed shape.

