## 💡 Notes

- The backend WebSocket consumer already has **all the infrastructure needed** for Option A and B. No Django/Python work is required.
- The `PaperDrawingEngine.getCanvasData()` method (line 2057) exports the full Paper.js project as JSON — this is what should be sent as the canvas snapshot.
- The `loadDrawingState()` method can receive and restore a Paper.js JSON export — this is how the receiver applies it.
- The `collaborationService` already has `sendMessage()` which can send arbitrary typed messages to the WebSocket.
